    <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="title:1;4:12">Creating an XML document for the Dynamic Table of Contexts</title>
    <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="shortdesc:1;5:16">In the Dynamic Table of Contexts (DToC) users can upload their own XML text. These
        XML documents need to be specially formatted in order to experience the full range of capabilities provided by DToC. </shortdesc>
    <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="taskbody:1;7:15">
        <context class="- topic/section task/context " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="context:1;8:18">
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="p:1;9:16">If you would like to follow along with these instructions you can download a template
                here: <xref href="http://cwrc.ca/templates/DToC_Document_Template.xml" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="xref:1;13:22">http://cwrc.ca/templates/DToC_Document_Template.xml</xref></p>
            <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="p:2;14:16">You can open this template in oXygen, TextEdit, TextWrangler, etc. </p>
        </context>
        <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="steps:1;16:16">
            <step class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="step:1;17:19">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="cmd:1;18:22">Open an application that allows you to create an XML document (oXygen,
                    TextWrangler, Textedit, etc.). The documentation presented here uses the Oxygen XML editor
                        <xref href="http://www.oxygenxml.com/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="xref:2;21:26">http://www.oxygenxml.com/</xref></cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="step:2;23:19">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="cmd:2;24:22"> Enter the XML declaration and TEI P5 schema definition<image placement="break" href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ad2aece60-4a43-48b2-8225-3a2e86a01398/datastream/OBJ/view" id="image_p24_kxn_c5" align="center" scale="85" class="- topic/image " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="image:1;26:74" scope="external"/></cmd>
                
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="step:3;29:19">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="cmd:3;30:22">Add the necessary information to your TEI header.</cmd>
                <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="info:1;31:23">The TEI Header allows you to define the title, publication information, and
                    source information about the document you are working on.</info>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="step:4;34:19">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="cmd:4;35:22">The &lt;div&gt; element is used to divide the corpus into sections or chapters. In the body section of your document, wrap div tags around each of your
                    chapters, or sections, that are to be separately itemized within the Table
                    of Contents. These &lt;div&gt; tags should include a ‘type’ attribute with the
                    value of ‘chapter’   &lt;div type='chapter'&gt;</cmd>
                <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="info:2;39:23">You define the div tags into chapters so that the different chapters will
                    appear in the Table of Contents feature in the DToC (see images below). This is
                    optional; if you don’t have multiple chapters you don't need this option.
                    However, if you do and do not include this ‘type’ attribute, the chapters
                    will blur together into one text without any distinct separations between your sections. All the div tags in the template
                    are predefined with "type='chapter'.<image placement="break" href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A23ad9b2a-0917-4f3c-a4c6-92c00c708b04/datastream/OBJ/view" id="image_odg_4gn_ht" align="center" class="- topic/image " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="image:2;46:63" scope="external"/></info>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="step:5;48:19">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="cmd:5;49:22">At the top of each chapter div, add the chapter’s author and title information
                    (see image above). <image placement="break" href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Aa3fffb29-edd3-4150-9049-91c41f3dcd3a/datastream/OBJ/view" id="image_o1f_1gn_ht" align="center" class="- topic/image " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="image:3;52:63" scope="external"/></cmd>
                <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="info:3;53:23">We have used TEI’s "head" tag to distinguish the headers from the body text;
                    we have also wrapped it in a bibliographic element. This ensures that any
                    information in a "head" tag will appear in the Table of Contents, as well as at the top
                    of the Reading Pane, depending on which chapter is being examined. <image placement="break" href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A5491f662-8261-42ba-a04c-a49379e10e46/datastream/OBJ/view" id="image_dzp_bhn_ht" align="center" scale="85" class="- topic/image " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="image:4;59:74" scope="external"/></info>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="step:6;61:19">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="cmd:6;62:22">Begin marking up your document. Here is an example of a simple XML document
                    that DToC will accept. <image placement="break" href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ae5c68101-74c5-46b8-8582-426be714ef6f/datastream/OBJ/view" id="image_djl_mhn_ht" align="center" class="- topic/image " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="image:5;65:63" scope="external"/></cmd>
                <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="info:4;66:23">This document only has one chapter associated with it and no index. For more information about
                    adding an index, see the “Adding an index” linked below.</info>
            </step>
            <step importance="optional" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="step:7;69:41">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="cmd:7;70:22"> If you would like to add additional chapters, copy the tags and text between
                    and including the &lt;div&gt; tags and paste that information below the last
                    &lt;div&gt; tag, then begin to fill in the information for your next chapter.
                        <image placement="break" href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A22b13354-ef15-4006-b2c0-628e474af8da/datastream/OBJ/view" id="image_dp4_c3n_ht" align="center" class="- topic/image " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="image:6;75:63" scope="external"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step importance="optional" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="step:8;77:41">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="cmd:8;78:22">You can now continue to mark up your text with XML tags (e.g. event, place,
                    organization, etc.). These tags will appear in the Tags column on the left side
                    of the DToC tool. <image placement="break" href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A2730f29d-dba5-47e0-a9e4-93e575007e45/datastream/OBJ/view" id="image_mqg_m3n_ht" align="center" class="- topic/image " xtrf="file:/Users/milovan/User%20Documentation/Documentation-all-user-documentation/DITA_Files-Various_Applications/DToC/CreatingXMLDoc.dita" xtrc="image:7;82:63" scope="external"/></cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
